organic_results.title: Effects of feeder patterns on students' transition to high school
organic_results.snippet: This article explores the transition between levels of schooling as a process in which students are moved between organizations. It focuses on a structural aspect of the transition process: students' patterns of movement from middle schools to high schools, which differentially affect students' academic adjustment to high school, depending how well the students were doing academically in middle school. Students who excelled in middle school seem to benefit from attending the same high school as a majority of their eighth-grade …
